Michael Faulkender of Maryland has been nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of the Treasury (Economic Policy). He is currently the Associate Dean of Masters Programs and a Professor of Finance at the Smith School of Business at the University of Maryland. Dr. Faulkender's research on capital structure, corporate liquidity, risk management, and executive compensation has been published in leading academic journals and has won numerous awards. He has previously held faculty positions at Washington University, Northwestern University, and the University of Pennsylvania. Dr. Faulkender holds a B.S. in Managerial Economics from the University of California, Davis and a Ph.D. in Finance from Northwestern University.